  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>to prep, so get your oven-proof dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-2-1691060265529-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-2-1691060265529-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-2-1691060265529-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-2-1691060265529-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-2-1691060265529-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let’s get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Add your<strong> diced beef</strong> to the dish with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong>, stir it all together, and cook for 2-3 min or until lightly browned all over</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1691060244163-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1691060244163-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1691060244163-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1691060244163-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1691060244163-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the beef is browning, peel and chop your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Top, tail and slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into discs (no need to peel!)</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife and discard the skins</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1691060246944-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1691060246944-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1691060246944-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1691060246944-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1691060246944-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> onion wedges</strong> to the dish with the<strong> chopped carrot</strong>, <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> and stir it all together</p><p>Add your <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, 450ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[600ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[750ml]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cover with the lid and put the dish in the oven for an initial 55 min</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1691060249334-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1691060249334-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1691060249334-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1691060249334-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1691060249334-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1691060252363-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1691060252363-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1691060252363-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1691060252363-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1691060252363-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the stew has been cooking for 25 min, add your<strong> white long grain rice </strong>to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with 300ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]<strong> </span>boiled water</strong></p><p>Cover tightly with <strong>tin foil</strong> and put the dish in the oven for 30 min or until all the water is absorbed and the rice is cooked – this is your <strong>baked rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1691060254762-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1691060254762-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1691060254762-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1691060254762-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1691060254762-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After an initial 55 min, add your<strong> mirin</strong>,<strong> soy sauce</strong>, <strong>ginger paste</strong> and  <strong>mangetout</strong> to the stew</p><p>Stir it all together, cover with the lid and return to the oven for a final 5 min or until the mangetout are tender with a slight bite – this is your<strong> oven-baked Japanese-style beef stew</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1691060259526-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1691060259526-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1691060259526-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1691060259526-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1691060259526-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To serve, set the <strong>oven-baked</strong> <strong>Japanese-style beef stew </strong>and<strong> baked rice</strong> in the centre of the table</p><p>Sprinkle your <strong>shichimi togarashi</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) all over the top</p><p>Let everyone dig in!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
